Origin

Not much is known about Harry's origin. He claims to be Prince Harry. He said his bodyguards grabbed him and his father, Prince Charles, and flew them to Balmoral, where there was meant to be a bunker. But they got swarmed by the Crossed as soon as the helicopter landed. He was found by other survivors and quickly adopted into the group. No proof of him being Prince Harry was ever given.

He died being sawed in half by the Crossed and was turned into a Crossed himself.

description:
Origin

Hiding for the Crossed with his girlfriend Penny, they decided to follow the main road for Glasgow. Not to travel on it, but use it as a guideline. Coming to a highway, Penny was infected by fresh Crossed blood. She decided to kill herself, rather than turning into a Crossed. Left alone, Ian wandered Scotland alone until he became part of a group of survivors.

He was the last one of his group to survive the chasing Crossed. He had one grenade to use on himself. It is unrevealed if he killed himself with the grenade while surrounded by his former teammates who had all turned into the Crossed.

deck: A comic book shop employee who was fired for selling stolen comics. He agreed to work for the Power Broker as part  in exchange for powers and employment.
description:
Story

Paul was a young adult who worked in a comic book shop, he was fired after his boss discovered Paul was stealing issues with variant covers, which he was selling to sustain his gaming hobby. Paul took notice of the Hench X App, and decided he could work as a super-villain mercenary, which he believed would certainly pay more than a minimum wage job. He also decided to take the opportunity to impress a girl he knew.

Paul attended one of the Power Broker's launch parties for the Hench X App, and he was chosen to be subjected to a process to become a super-villain on the spot. After Paul became the new Plantman, Ant-Man arrived to the scene to interrogate the Power Broker for personal matters. The Power Broker decided to use Ant-Man's presence to his advantage, and pitch Plantman against him for publicity.

Ant-Man used Platman's inexperience to his advatange, and knocked him down after having his ants eat most of Paul's green arsenal.

At some point in time, Paul was imprisoned by S.H.I.E.L.D. in Pleasant Hill, a super-prison designed to turn their inmates into model citizens with the use of a Cosmic Cube. He was turned into a TV repairman.

After a revolt incited by Baron Zemo which led to a breakout, Plantman escaped from Pleasant Hill. He later heeded Zemo's call to form the "New Masters" alongside Firebrand and Flying Tiger. When Captain America and his allies attacked Zemo, Paul surrendered without a fight, hoping it would be beneficial for his parole hearing.
